WEBVTT

00:28.994 --> 00:30.116
Welcome to God Day.

00:30.918 --> 00:45.248
I'm Derek Walker, the pastor of the Oxford Bible Church and I want to take you to John chapter 5 and one of the great healing miracles in the Gospel of John, the healing at the pool of Bethesda.

00:46.089 --> 00:50.258
And all of John's miracles are called signs.

00:50.818 --> 00:54.121
the signs that Jesus did.

00:54.161 --> 00:59.266
This is the word called semion, which really means it's a miracle with a message.

01:00.087 --> 01:05.953
And we are meant to learn the message from the miracle and apply it to us.

01:07.234 --> 01:16.864
And basically through these signs, God is declaring, Christ is declaring what He will do for us, if we trust in Him.

01:17.805 --> 01:19.346
At the end of the Gospel of John,

01:20.386 --> 01:35.667
It says that John's gospel was written and these signs were written that we might believe in Jesus as the Christ, the Son of God, and through believing we might have life in his name.

01:36.308 --> 01:48.946
And it's basically saying these signs reveal the name or the nature, the power of Christ and through believing in him, through these signs,

01:49.538 --> 01:58.513
we are saved and we actually receive the blessing that that miracle reveals.

01:59.054 --> 02:13.298
And so while we read about this man who was probably paralyzed at the pool of Bethesda, we need to remember this is a picture of us and what Jesus comes for us to save us.

02:13.410 --> 02:19.517
And so through this story, this is also about what Jesus wants to do for each one of us.

02:20.778 --> 02:26.104
So if we go to John chapter five verse one, it says, after this, there was a feast of the Jews.

02:26.865 --> 02:29.067
I personally think it's probably tabernacles.

02:29.968 --> 02:34.093
And Jesus went up to Jerusalem to keep the feast.

02:34.914 --> 02:42.322
Now there is in Jerusalem by the sheep gate, a pool, which is called in Hebrew, Bethesda, having five

02:42.594 --> 03:00.196
Now this is a lovely example of the accuracy of the Bible because this is saying that by the sheep gate, the sheep gate, which is mentioned in Nehemiah three times, it's on the north side of the temple where the sheep for the sacrifice are brought in through that sheep gate.

03:00.236 --> 03:08.627
So it's saying that near the north gate of the temple mount, there should be a pool.

03:09.508 --> 03:11.090
This pool

03:11.394 --> 03:34.514
strangely has five porches and so for a long time people said you know this is just the bible making stuff up you know the liberals would say that and then in 1888 they actually started digging near St Anne's church

03:34.626 --> 03:44.415
which was a crusader church in that region because they found a mosaic when they uncovered a mosaic with a picture of this miracle.

03:45.196 --> 03:52.223
And so they started digging in the grounds and they discovered, lo and behold, two pools.

03:53.664 --> 04:04.114
What it really is is two large pools with a dam one above the other, the northern pool and a southern pool and a dam between them.

04:04.834 --> 04:19.133
And actually, it had five porches exactly the way the Bible described, because you would have porticoes, you know, colonnaded roofs going all the way around the two pools on all four sides.

04:19.614 --> 04:24.961
And then another portico across the dam that was in the middle.

04:25.802 --> 04:31.009
And hence, you have the five porticoes and the Bible was proved to be accurate.

04:31.770 --> 04:34.514
And then they also found remains of a great

04:34.690 --> 04:43.262
Byzantine church that was built on that spot because it was known as a well-known, you know, for that miracle.

04:44.203 --> 04:47.587
And Jerome mentions this place too.

04:47.648 --> 04:50.972
And so why were there two pools?

04:51.132 --> 05:04.210
Well, this was actually because in the first century, there may have been originally one pool that was a reservoir for rainwater and so on, and water could then be supplied to

05:04.322 --> 05:05.744
to Jerusalem.

05:07.806 --> 05:11.090
But then in the first century, they got very keen on mikvah.

05:11.630 --> 05:18.819
And this is the ritual washing that the Jews had to go through every day, and especially to go onto the temple.

05:19.700 --> 05:24.906
And these mikvah required, you could only be cleansed if there was, in a sense, running water.

05:25.967 --> 05:31.954
And so the ideal one, there was one on the south end, which was the pool of Siloam,

05:32.226 --> 05:36.452
that operated as a mikvah, it had running water from the gihon spring.

05:37.153 --> 05:56.242
But there's no spring on the north side, so what they would do in their laws of mikvah, they would actually have, you can have a reservoir and then as long as you kept feeding water from the upper reservoir into the lower pool, then that counted as running water

05:56.354 --> 06:00.301
And then so people would go and they could wash in that.

06:00.601 --> 06:09.596
And for the crowds of people, especially at feast time, going to the temple, they needed a big mikvah like the pool of Bethesda.

06:09.837 --> 06:16.027
And so it functioned as a mikvah, but also it became known as a place of healing.

06:16.708 --> 06:22.418
In fact, Bethesda means house of mercy or house of the outpouring.

06:23.010 --> 06:24.672
the outpouring of God's mercy.

06:24.712 --> 06:29.377
So it got a reputation that people were healed there.

06:30.078 --> 06:32.982
In fact, that's part of the passage that we're going to see now.

06:33.903 --> 06:42.012
And so archeology has confirmed the Bible about the pool of Bethesda, and it's a great place to go if you do a trip to Israel.

06:43.153 --> 06:44.895
Go through the entrance.

06:45.456 --> 06:50.642
You go off the Temple Mount, cross the street, and you go into

06:50.786 --> 06:54.491
the grounds of St. Anne's Church, and then you'll discover it there.

06:55.392 --> 07:14.418
And so it says, in these lay a great multitude of sick people, blind, lame, paralyzed, and all these sick people were looking for their healing, and also that was kind of the closest spot they could go to, close to the temple.

07:14.626 --> 07:29.280
And so it says that they were waiting for the moving of the water for an angel, went down at a certain time into the pool and stirred up the water and then whoever stepped in first after the stirring of the water was made well of whatever disease he had.

07:30.120 --> 07:42.952
And so there was a belief developed and it could well be, you know, that God did this as a supernatural thing, that an angel stirred up the water and then you would get healed.

07:42.993 --> 07:44.594
Other people believed that

07:44.930 --> 07:56.366
that this was the kind of story that grew up, but the moving of the water is when they opened up the dam and released some more water and whatever.

07:56.486 --> 08:05.178
But anyway, people had an expectation of being healed, but now we focus on a certain man.

08:05.979 --> 08:13.970
But we see this crowd of sick people around this pool, hoping against hope for a miracle.

08:14.914 --> 08:24.007
And this represents sinful and sick humanity, hoping for some kind of miracle in their life.

08:25.188 --> 08:27.712
And now we focus in on a certain man.

08:27.772 --> 08:30.956
And again, this man represents all of us really.

08:31.417 --> 08:35.963
It says a certain man was there who had an infirmity, 38 years.

08:36.524 --> 08:37.605
Now that's a long time.

08:38.527 --> 08:41.911
And he had this thing for most of his life.

08:42.492 --> 08:43.954
And I think we're told this,

08:44.546 --> 08:47.409
just to see that this was not some passing sickness.

08:48.270 --> 08:57.239
This is a permanent condition that this man is in, that there was no human help available to him.

08:57.679 --> 09:02.144
We're going to see that behind this sickness was sin, actually, in his case.

09:02.945 --> 09:04.546
And this is a picture of us.

09:04.666 --> 09:09.291
We are sick and we are because of sin.

09:10.192 --> 09:12.114
The whole human race is in this

09:12.322 --> 09:21.194
state of sickness and because of this sickness he was paralyzed which is a picture of the fact that we can't do what we ought to do.

09:21.234 --> 09:22.856
We can't walk in God's will.

09:23.317 --> 09:32.249
We're paralyzed because of the fall, because of sin and we are sick in our being and our physical body.

09:33.070 --> 09:42.002
The fullness of our body is a picture of that and there is no human help available as we see in this story.

09:43.170 --> 09:45.353
He was, in a sense, a hopeless case.

09:46.254 --> 09:55.544
And he might have been on the point of just giving up all hope, all hope of help, 38 years.

09:56.305 --> 10:10.802
And then it says, when Jesus saw him lying there, and I love that, God had sent Jesus to this pool, and Jesus saw this man lying there in his sickness, and

10:11.298 --> 10:15.324
Jesus came comes to us too, and he sees us.

10:16.265 --> 10:16.986
He sees us.

10:17.867 --> 10:19.930
He came to seek and save the lost.

10:20.230 --> 10:24.236
Praise God, Jesus saw you in your desperate state.

10:25.417 --> 10:27.020
And he did something about it.

10:27.881 --> 10:30.544
And Jesus comes to everyone in this way.

10:30.584 --> 10:35.351
He saw him lying there, and he knew that he had been in that condition a long time.

10:35.952 --> 10:38.676
See, Jesus saw us, saw him, and he knew.

10:38.696 --> 10:40.498
He knew intuitively.

10:41.282 --> 10:45.108
that he was in that lost situation.

10:45.488 --> 10:54.121
Jesus saw us, he knows our lostness, our need, and he loves us, praise God.

10:54.422 --> 10:58.768
And so he said to him a curious question.

10:59.029 --> 11:01.532
He said, do you want to be made well?

11:02.334 --> 11:05.298
And you might think, you know, that's a silly question.

11:05.698 --> 11:07.962
Do you want, of course, he would want to be made well.

11:08.403 --> 11:10.526
But actually, it isn't an automatic thing.

11:10.586 --> 11:13.912
Sometimes people don't really want to be well.

11:14.533 --> 11:18.600
Sometimes people like to be the victim.

11:18.640 --> 11:18.760
Why?

11:18.820 --> 11:23.608
Because you have no responsibilities.

11:23.708 --> 11:25.231
Everyone's sympathetic to you.

11:25.291 --> 11:29.017
Nobody expects anything of you because you're sick.

11:29.478 --> 11:31.922
And some people are comfortable

11:32.450 --> 11:47.346
in that situation of just lying there, not having to do anything because if you get well, then now you're expected to take up the responsibilities of life, you're expected to do things.

11:47.626 --> 12:02.002
And so because of that, it isn't an automatic thing that people do want to be healed because they might be comfortable, you know, just receiving help and not having to do anything themselves.

12:02.114 --> 12:04.918
And so there's a great trap in that.

12:06.320 --> 12:14.371
And so first of all, Jesus asks this provocative question, and this particular man does want to get well.

12:15.772 --> 12:20.058
But even so, he was in this paralyzed state.

12:20.198 --> 12:23.102
It would have been easy for him to become passive.

12:23.883 --> 12:31.794
And by coming to him and saying, do you want to get well, what Jesus was doing was activating his hope

12:32.322 --> 12:38.690
and causing his will to come alive.

12:39.491 --> 12:47.561
This is the first step to getting better is you've got to want to be set free.

12:49.062 --> 12:55.390
It's a picture of us in our sin because Jesus comes to each one of us and says, do you want to be saved?

12:56.151 --> 12:58.213
Do you want me to save you from your sin?

12:59.075 --> 13:01.938
And people don't necessarily want.

13:02.178 --> 13:03.239
to be saved, do they?

13:03.940 --> 13:05.943
No, because they enjoy their sin too much.

13:06.644 --> 13:11.450
They don't want to be free from their addiction because they've got used to it.

13:11.630 --> 13:13.112
It's part of their comfort life.

13:13.893 --> 13:16.536
And so it is a very relevant question.

13:16.636 --> 13:22.063
God comes to us and says to us, you are lost in your sin, you are dying.

13:23.465 --> 13:24.806
Do you want to be saved?

13:26.148 --> 13:28.211
And that's a big question we have to ask ourselves.

13:28.531 --> 13:30.994
Do I want to be free from that sin?

13:31.426 --> 13:32.948
Do I want to be saved?"

13:34.210 --> 13:44.222
And what Jesus is doing by that is activating this man's will, first of all, to say, yes, I want, I want to be saved.

13:44.242 --> 13:50.150
And what Jesus is also doing is directing that man's attention to himself.

13:51.732 --> 13:59.442
As we're going to see, this man did want to be helped, but he had put his trust in other people who let him down.

14:00.130 --> 14:07.177
And Jesus is now redirecting his faith toward Jesus himself.

14:07.678 --> 14:10.240
You see, we've got to want to be saved.

14:10.721 --> 14:14.665
And secondly, we have got to direct our will toward God.

14:14.725 --> 14:19.330
And the Bible says, all who call on the name of the Lord shall be saved.

14:19.850 --> 14:21.272
We've got to want to be saved.

14:21.392 --> 14:27.538
And then we've got to align ourselves with God's will, as we're going to see.

14:28.162 --> 14:33.450
Jesus is actually saying through this, I want to heal you.

14:34.171 --> 14:35.172
I want to save you.

14:36.414 --> 14:37.716
Do you want to be saved?

14:38.157 --> 14:39.358
Do you want to be healed?

14:39.999 --> 14:41.462
That's how Jesus comes to us.

14:42.102 --> 14:46.249
And he's asking us to respond and to say yes.

14:47.290 --> 14:53.760
And when we turn our will toward Jesus in faith and say yes, I want you to heal me.

14:54.120 --> 14:55.442
I want you to save me.

14:55.842 --> 15:02.229
praise God, then that gives him permission to do his miracle in our life.

15:02.910 --> 15:08.916
So while we're looking to man to be saved or to ourselves to be saved, it doesn't work.

15:08.936 --> 15:12.000
But Jesus comes and says, do you want me to save you?

15:12.340 --> 15:13.581
Do you want me to heal you?

15:14.142 --> 15:18.086
And like this man, we look up to Jesus and we say, yes.

15:19.608 --> 15:23.452
And that's how Jesus prepared him to receive this miracle.

15:24.273 --> 15:25.074
Praise God.

15:25.154 --> 15:30.904
Jesus just picked one man out of the crowd and came to him.

15:31.465 --> 15:34.450
But I believe that's a picture of what he does to each one of us.

15:34.510 --> 15:41.282
He comes to us and some people, when he asked that question, they say, no, Jesus, I just leave me alone.

15:42.625 --> 15:47.894
But others respond like this man and they say, yes, I want you to save me.

15:48.475 --> 15:50.258
Let's see what happens in the story.

15:51.522 --> 15:52.663
do you want to be made well?"

15:52.683 --> 15:56.027
And the sick man answered him, well, it's a bit of a roundabout answer.

15:56.388 --> 16:03.416
He says, sir, I have got no man to put me into the pool when the waters stirred up, but when I'm coming, another steps down before me.

16:04.777 --> 16:11.185
But although it's a kind of excuse he gives, but he is basically saying, yes, I want to be healed.

16:12.767 --> 16:15.730
It's just that all my efforts have come to nothing.

16:16.002 --> 16:17.324
I've trusted in myself.

16:17.384 --> 16:18.666
I've trusted in other people.

16:18.986 --> 16:20.468
It's all come to nothing.

16:20.488 --> 16:22.411
But I do want to be healed.

16:22.431 --> 16:27.257
And so what Jesus has done here is got him into position now.

16:27.618 --> 16:31.423
Now this person realizes no one else can save me.

16:31.823 --> 16:32.764
Man can't save me.

16:32.845 --> 16:33.966
I can't save myself.

16:34.307 --> 16:38.072
But here is one who is saying he can save me.

16:38.993 --> 16:45.842
And he is saying, yes, I want you to help me, to heal me.

16:45.954 --> 16:52.301
And Jesus then immediately responded by saying, rise, take up your bed and walk.

16:53.282 --> 16:58.048
And now Jesus speaks this word, rise.

16:58.128 --> 16:59.289
And it seems impossible.

16:59.510 --> 17:00.991
How can he possibly rise up?

17:01.252 --> 17:02.133
He's paralyzed.

17:03.294 --> 17:13.586
But one wonderful thing, whenever God commands us to do something, that command is also a promise because in his command,

17:13.794 --> 17:16.998
in his word is the power to do what he's telling you to do.

17:17.599 --> 17:24.388
God tells you to do sometimes something that's impossible, but he's not unjust.

17:24.428 --> 17:26.270
He wouldn't ask you to do something you can't do.

17:26.590 --> 17:32.118
So in other words, when he tells you to do something, the power is in his word to do it.

17:32.438 --> 17:39.127
So the moment Jesus said rise, resurrection power was released to that man.

17:39.607 --> 17:41.810
And as that man looked to Jesus,

17:41.954 --> 17:51.186
And Jesus said, rise, he put his trust in Jesus, and that resurrection power came into him, and he was able to rise.

17:51.887 --> 17:52.508
Praise God.

17:52.989 --> 17:56.393
And this is a picture of the new birth.

17:56.874 --> 17:57.915
This is a picture.

17:57.955 --> 18:00.258
Here we are, paralyzed in our sin.

18:00.719 --> 18:01.961
We can't save ourself.

18:02.001 --> 18:03.142
Man can't save us.

18:03.743 --> 18:06.947
Jesus comes to us and says, do you want me to save you?

18:06.987 --> 18:08.670
And we say, yes.

18:09.551 --> 18:11.954
And then his resurrection power.

18:12.610 --> 18:22.519
is released into our hearts that causes our spirits to be raised from death to life, praise God.

18:22.960 --> 18:30.347
And then he also says, praise God, he doesn't just say rise, he says, take up your bed and walk.

18:30.927 --> 18:36.412
In other words, he says, leave your past life behind where you're just lying in bed all the time.

18:36.473 --> 18:42.258
He says, take up your bed, take up your responsibilities in life, take up

18:42.594 --> 18:46.639
the will of God for your life and walk.

18:47.540 --> 18:52.627
Go into a new life, walk in the will of God, praise God.

18:52.767 --> 19:02.579
And by saying those words, Jesus imparted his power to that man to not just rise up, but also to walk and to live a new life.

19:02.599 --> 19:03.640
And that's what he does for us.

19:03.680 --> 19:05.042
When we receive him,

19:05.410 --> 19:20.491
We don't just have our spirits raised from the dead, but he empowers us now by his spirit within us to live a new life, to pick up the will of God and to walk in the Spirit, praise God.

19:20.531 --> 19:25.598
And that is a picture of salvation, praise God.

19:26.118 --> 19:32.887
However hopeless this man was, 38 years, Jesus can do that miracle.

19:33.188 --> 19:34.770
We were lost in our sin.

19:34.850 --> 19:43.258
We were paralyzed, but Jesus came and raised us up and caused us to live a new life.

19:43.318 --> 19:45.961
This is a sign, miracle, praise God.

19:46.541 --> 19:51.546
And then it says, immediately, the man was made well, took up his bed and walked.

19:51.706 --> 19:56.050
The power of God was released through Jesus' words and he walked.

19:56.731 --> 20:04.178
And then as we read on it says, that day was the Sabbath, the Jews therefore, which meant the Jewish establishment,

20:04.258 --> 20:06.560
said to him who was cured, it's the Sabbath.

20:06.640 --> 20:08.942
It's not lawful for you to carry your bed.

20:09.383 --> 20:21.354
He wasn't actually breaking the Sabbath in God's sight, but he was breaking some of the Jews' petty regulations they had built up about the Sabbath that you can't carry anything from one place to another.

20:21.394 --> 20:26.819
And so they criticized him rather than being pleased that he's healed.

20:27.800 --> 20:30.002
They criticized him for carrying his bed.

20:30.042 --> 20:34.066
And the bed, by the way, is just a rolled up mat, really.

20:35.266 --> 20:41.274
He answered them saying, he who made me well said to me, take up your bed and walk.

20:42.135 --> 20:45.420
And then they asked him, who is the man who said to you, take up your bed and walk?

20:46.040 --> 20:51.367
But the one who was healed didn't know who it was, for Jesus had withdrawn a multitude being in that place.

20:52.669 --> 20:58.377
Afterward, Jesus found him in the temple and said to him, see you have been made well.

20:59.659 --> 21:02.983
Sin no more, lest a worse thing come upon you.

21:03.363 --> 21:05.266
So notice that

21:05.826 --> 21:08.049
Jesus connects his sickness with sin.

21:08.610 --> 21:14.599
And he's saying, don't go back to that sin that got you in this mess in the first place that you've been in.

21:14.659 --> 21:18.525
If you sin, sin no more.

21:19.085 --> 21:22.290
And he empowers him not to sin through those words.

21:22.370 --> 21:24.874
Sin no more, that's the worst thing come upon you.

21:25.495 --> 21:33.266
And so this actually shows that when Jesus healed him, he also released him from the power of sin.

21:33.570 --> 21:44.824
And so behind his sickness, again, the picture of this is mankind who is sick, outwardly sick, mentally sick and so forth, sick in his soul.

21:45.785 --> 21:48.428
But the root cause of it is sin.

21:49.049 --> 21:56.378
It's sin ultimately that brings the curse of sickness and so forth in our lives.

21:56.478 --> 22:03.346
And so when Jesus healed him, this is a picture of us being delivered from sin, forgiven of sin.

22:03.682 --> 22:11.212
released from sin so that we can now walk in the will of God and be in health, praise God.

22:11.553 --> 22:14.337
This is a picture of salvation.

22:15.078 --> 22:16.960
Jesus doesn't just heal us outwardly.

22:17.421 --> 22:22.888
He gives us the power and the forgiveness of that sin, praise God.

22:23.249 --> 22:28.917
But he warns him, he says, if you go back to a sinful lifestyle, something worse will happen.

22:29.718 --> 22:32.882
And that man then, I believe,

22:33.570 --> 22:38.296
He departed, it says, and he told the Jews that it was Jesus that made him well.

22:38.937 --> 22:41.761
And again, he wasn't blaming Jesus for making him carry his bed.

22:42.202 --> 22:44.645
He was giving glory to Jesus for making him well.

22:45.306 --> 22:47.829
The Jews persecuted Jesus for that reason.

22:48.350 --> 22:48.570
Why?

22:48.650 --> 22:50.493
Because he healed on the Sabbath.

22:50.873 --> 22:54.819
They sought to kill him, it says, because he had done these things on the Sabbath.

22:55.419 --> 22:58.283
But Jesus answered, he actually upped the ante.

22:59.385 --> 23:03.410
He says, my father, my father,

23:03.874 --> 23:09.482
See, that language meant that he was the Son of God in a special way.

23:10.304 --> 23:13.408
My father has been working till now and I've been working.

23:14.049 --> 23:21.560
He is saying, there are many arguments why Jesus could rightly heal on the Sabbath without breaking the Sabbath.

23:22.221 --> 23:28.911
But first of all, it was an act of mercy and that trumped any ceremonial Sabbath law.

23:29.232 --> 23:32.136
But in this case, he's claiming deity.

23:32.537 --> 23:33.458
He's saying,

23:33.538 --> 23:35.421
My father doesn't keep the Sabbath.

23:35.481 --> 23:42.612
God doesn't keep the Sabbath because God is constantly working, sustaining the universe and also redeeming people.

23:42.652 --> 23:44.054
He doesn't take a day off.

23:45.556 --> 23:48.921
Jesus said elsewhere, the Sabbath is made for man, not man for the Sabbath.

23:50.303 --> 23:54.370
And Jesus is saying, just as my father's working, so I'm working.

23:55.131 --> 23:59.858
And the Jews understood that by calling God his special father,

24:00.226 --> 24:15.524
and putting him in the same category of God as not having to keep the Sabbath, then the Jews sought all the more to kill him because he not only broke the Sabbath, but also said that God was his father, making himself equal with God.

24:16.565 --> 24:27.218
And then let's just point out that in the next teaching, Jesus gave the message of the miracle and he says,

24:27.362 --> 24:37.058
in verse 20, for the father loves the son and shows him all things that he himself does and he will show him greater works than these that you may marvel.

24:37.559 --> 24:46.634
